ls only","Myoepithelial cells only","Squamous cells","Lymphoid cells"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAdenoid cystic carcinoma is a type of salivary gland tumour that is characterised by the presence of both \u003Cstrong\u003Eductal and myoepithelial cells\u003C/strong\u003E. These two cell types contribute to the tumour\u0027s distinctive histological pattern, which includes cribriform, tubular, and solid growth patterns. The combination of these cells is essential for the diagnosis of adenoid cystic carcinoma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDuctal cells only\u003C/strong\u003E would not account for the full histological appearance of adenoid cystic carcinoma, as myoepithelial cells are also a key component.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMyoepithelial cells only\u003C/strong\u003E would similarly not provide the complete cellular architecture seen in adenoid cystic carcinoma, which requires both ductal and myoepithelial cells.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESquamous cells\u003C/strong\u003E are not typically found in adenoid cystic carcinoma, as this tumour arises from glandular tissue rather than squamous epithelium.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELymphoid cells\u003C/strong\u003E are not a characteristic component of adenoid cystic carcinoma, although they may be present in other types of salivary gland tumours or in reactive lymphoid tissue surrounding the tumour.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Adenoid cystic carcinoma of the parotid gland is composed of both ductal and myoepithelial cells.","The presence of both cell types contributes to the characteristic histological appearance of adenoid cystic carcinoma.","Understanding the cellular composition of salivary gland tumors aids in diagnosis and management."],"references":["\u0022Adenoid cystic carcinoma\u0022 by Nephron is licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported license. https://commons.m.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Adenoid_cystic_carcinoma_-_high_mag.jpg","Ammad Ud Din M, Shaikh H. Adenoid Cystic Cancer. 2023 Apr 14. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32491778.","Saleh E, Ukwas A. Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma of Salivary Glands: A Ten-Year Review and an Assessment of the Current Management, Surgery, Radiotherapy, and Chemotherapy. Int J Otolaryngol. 2023 Apr 29;2023:7401458. doi: 10.1155/2023/7401458. PMID: 37159817; PMCID: PMC10163974."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51419"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15250"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21137"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21137","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21137"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/9Q2jj8o5M9Pmyv9r9jkdwijPMQcgwy.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/9Q2jj8o5M9Pmyv9r9jkdwijPMQcgwy.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1500,"height":1000}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51419","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51419"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-28T11:53:23+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-28T11:53:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7941"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65970"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","pos